<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#ecd0eae46413ef587b82e45f1b4bd389>.
<#ecd0eae46413ef587b82e45f1b4bd389> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://opendata-api.malmo.se/dataset/82b9290d-bd82-4611-ae28-161f95c71339>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-05-11T07:12:35.864Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#ecd0eae46413ef587b82e45f1b4bd389> {
<https://opendata-api.malmo.se/dataset/82b9290d-bd82-4611-ae28-161f95c71339> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Malmö stad", "restroom", "toalett", "toilet", "wc";
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accrualPeriodicity> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/frequency/MONTHLY>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> "82b9290d-bd82-4611-ae28-161f95c71339";
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/SWE>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <https://malmo.se/>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Denna datamängd innehåller offentliga toaletter som förvaltas av Malmö stad.\n\n__Attribut__  \n  \n+ `source` [organisationsnr för förvaltande myndighet]  \n+ `name` [den offentliga toalettens namn]  \n+ `description` [kort beskrivning]  \n+ `id` [identifierare för den offentliga toaletten]  \n+ `opens` [öppningstid]  \n+ `closes` [stängningstid]  \n+ `service` [underhållsfrekvens]  \n+ `fee` [avgiftsbelagd]  \n+ `rwc` [tillgänglighetsanpassad]  \n+ `amenities` [befintliga bekvämligheter]  \n+ `street` [gatuadress]  \n+ `postalcode` [postnummer]  \n+ `city` [postort]  \n+ `phone` [telefonnummer för frågor, synpunkter, felanmälan]  \n+ `email` [e-postadress för vidare kontakt]  \n+ `URL` [ingångssida för mer information]  \n+ `image` [länkar till bilder]  \n+ `geometry` [typ: Point, CRS: WGS84]  \n\nAttributen följer i stort [Specifikation för offentliga toaletter - version 0.9](https://lankadedata.se/spec/public-toilets/), framtagen av Nationell Dataverkstad. Specifikationens fält för longitud, latitud är här anpassade till GeoJSONs __geometry__-attribut.  \n\nMalmö stads offentliga toaletter kan ha varierande öppettider beroende på säsong, vilket inte kan representeras på ett bra sätt enligt nuvarande specifikation. Toaletter med varierande öppettider saknar därför uppgift om öppettid.  "@sv, "This dataset contains public toilets managed by the city of Malmö.\n\n**Attribute**\n\n  * `source` [organizational number of managing authority]\n  * `name` [public toilet name]\n  * `description` [short description]\n  * `id` [identifier for the public toilet]\n  * `opens` [opening time]\n  * `closes` [closing time]\n  * `service` [maintenance frequency]\n  * `fee` [fee]\n  * `rwc` [accessible]\n  * `amenities` [existing amenities]\n  * `street` [street address]\n  * `postalcode` [postal code]\n  * `city` ​​[postal town]\n  * `phone` [phone number for questions, comments, bug reports]\n  * `email` [email address for further contact]\n  * `URL` [entry page for more information]\n  * `image` [links to images]\n  * `geometry` [type: Point, CRS: WGS84]\n\nThe attributes largely follow [the Specification for public toilets - version\n0.9](https://lankadedata.se/spec/public%2dtoilets/) , developed by the\nNational Data Workshop. The specification's fields for longitude and latitude\nare here adapted to GeoJSON's **geometry** attributes.\n\nMalmö City's public toilets may have varying opening hours depending on the\nseason, which cannot be represented well according to the current\nspecification. Toilets with varying opening hours therefore lack information\nabout opening hours.\n\n"@en, "Dette datasæt indeholder offentlige toiletter, der forvaltes af Malmø by.\n\n**Attribut**\n\n  * `source` [organisationsnummer for forvaltningsmyndighed]\n  * `name` [navn på offentligt toilet]\n  * `description` [kort beskrivelse]\n  * `id` [identifikator for det offentlige toilet]\n  * `opens` [åbningstid]\n  * `closes` [lukketid]\n  * `service` [vedligeholdelsesfrekvens]\n  * `fee` [gebyr]\n  * `rwc` [tilgængelig]\n  * `amenities` [eksisterende faciliteter]\n  * `street` [gadeadresse]\n  * `postalcode` [postnummer]\n  * `city` [postby]\n  * `phone` [telefonnummer til spørgsmål, kommentarer, fejlrapporter]\n  * `email` [e-mailadresse for yderligere kontakt]\n  * `URL` [indgangsside for mere information]\n  * `image` [links til billeder]\n  * `geometry` [type: Punkt, CRS: WGS84]\n\nAttributterne følger i vid udstrækning [Specifikationen for offentlige\ntoiletter - version 0.9](https://lankadedata.se/spec/public%2dtoilets/) ,\nudviklet af National Data Workshop. Specifikationens felter for længdegrad og\nbreddegrad er her tilpasset GeoJSONs **geometriattributter** .\n\nMalmø Bys offentlige toiletter kan have varierende åbningstider afhængigt af\nsæsonen, hvilket ikke kan repræsenteres godt i henhold til den nuværende\nspecifikation. Toiletter med varierende åbningstider mangler derfor\ninformation om åbningstider.\n\n"@da;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://www.geonames.org/2692965/malmoe.html>, _:b0__523.
_:b0__523 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#bbox> "POLYGON((12.8850967451 55.6421476735,13.1517619812 55.6421476735,13.1517619812 55.5022773196,12.8850967451 55.5022773196,12.8850967451 55.6421476735))"^^<http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#wktLiteral>;
    a <http://purl.org/dc/terms/Location>.
<https://opendata-api.malmo.se/dataset/82b9290d-bd82-4611-ae28-161f95c71339> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/290/resource/abd7da407bcfbc956fd6c0e91189412f>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://opendata-api.malmo.se/dataset/82b9290d-bd82-4611-ae28-161f95c71339/resource/81b70be0-1860-467f-bfcc-5bf70d094dd0>, <https://opendata-api.malmo.se/dataset/82b9290d-bd82-4611-ae28-161f95c71339/resource/dcaba0b6-1da4-4363-b826-538bb39d1581>, <https://opendata-api.malmo.se/dataset/82b9290d-bd82-4611-ae28-161f95c71339/resource/247860ce-9413-405e-ab54-39892cdb0349>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2025-11-06"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2026-05-10T18:00:21.195096"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Offentliga toaletter"@sv, "Public toilets"@en, "Offentlige toiletter"@da;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/SOCI>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/conformsTo> <https://lankadedata.se/spec/public-toilets/>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#efea55f6687fd7e3322b2d2bc15836c8>.
<#efea55f6687fd7e3322b2d2bc15836c8> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Update>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://opendata-api.malmo.se/dataset/a6ae4550-f95d-4bf2-a6bf-740592a61c15>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-05-11T07:12:35.865Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#efea55f6687fd7e3322b2d2bc15836c8> {
<https://opendata-api.malmo.se/dataset/a6ae4550-f95d-4bf2-a6bf-740592a61c15> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Malmö stad", "badvatten", "havsbad", "strandbad";
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accrualPeriodicity> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/frequency/CONT>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> "a6ae4550-f95d-4bf2-a6bf-740592a61c15";
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/SWE>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <https://malmo.se/>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Malmö stad mäter vattentemperaturer i havet vid ett antal badplatser. Mätningarna görs med temperatursensorer som är placerade nära ytan (optimalt på ca 50 cm djup) några 50-tal meter ut från land. Sensorerna meddelar i normalfallet temperatur ett antal gånger i timmen och medelvärdet per timme är det som publiceras i denna datamängd.  \nFelaktiga mätvärden är ovanliga men kan förekomma om sensordriften störs.\n\nResurserna består dels av GeoJSON-filer (Platser ÅÅÅÅ-MM.geojson) som månadsvis visar de sensorer som varit aktiva och deras ungefärliga placering. Tillhörande mätvärden per månad finns i CSV-filer (Vattentemperaturer ÅÅÅÅ-MM.csv).  \n\nMätvärdesfiler följer [FIWAREs specifikation för WaterQualityObserved](https://fiware-datamodels.readthedocs.io/en/stable/Environment/WaterQualityObserved/doc/spec/index.html).  \n\n__Attribut Platser__  \n  \n+ `id` [sensoridentitet]  \n+ `address` [sensorns placering (text)]  \n+ `geometry` [sensorns ungefärliga position, typ: Polygon, CRS: WGS84]  \n  \n__Attribut Vattentemperaturer__  \n\n+ `type` [alltid \"WaterQualityObserved\"]  \n+ `id` [sensoridentitet]  \n+ `address` [sensorns placering (text)]  \n+ `dateObserved` [datum och timme (format ISO 8601) då mätvärdet rapporterats]  \n+ `temperature` [uppmätt temperatur i grader Celsius]  \n"@sv, "The city of Malmö measures water temperatures in the sea at a number of\nbathing areas. The measurements are made with temperature sensors that are\nplaced close to the surface (optimally at a depth of about 50 cm) some 50\nmeters from land. The sensors normally report the temperature a number of\ntimes per hour and the average value per hour is what is published in this\ndataset.  \nIncorrect measurement values ​​are uncommon but can occur if sensor operation\nis disrupted.\n\nThe resources consist of GeoJSON files (Locations YYYY-MM.geojson) that show\nthe sensors that have been active and their approximate location on a monthly\nbasis. Corresponding measurement values ​​per month are available in CSV files\n(Water Temperatures YYYY-MM.csv).\n\nMeasurement value files follow [FIWARE's specification for\nWaterQualityObserved](https://fiware%2ddatamodels.readthedocs.io/en/stable/Environment/WaterQualityObserved/doc/spec/index.html)\n.\n\n**Attributes Locations**\n\n  * `id` [sensor identity]\n  * `address` [sensor location (text)]\n  * `geometry` [approximate position of the sensor, type: Polygon, CRS: WGS84]\n\n**Attributes Water temperatures**\n\n  * `type` [always \"WaterQualityObserved\"]\n  * `id` [sensor identity]\n  * `address` [sensor location (text)]\n  * `dateObserved` [date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the measurement value was reported]\n  * `temperature` [measured temperature in degrees Celsius]\n\n"@en, "Malmø kommune måler vandtemperaturen i havet ved en række badeområder.\nMålingerne foretages med temperatursensorer, der er placeret tæt på overfladen\n(optimalt set i en dybde på ca. 50 cm) cirka 50 meter fra land. Sensorerne\nrapporterer normalt temperaturen et antal gange i timen, og gennemsnitsværdien\npr. time er den, der offentliggøres i dette datasæt.  \nForkerte måleværdier er usædvanlige, men kan forekomme, hvis sensorens drift\nafbrydes.\n\nRessourcerne består af GeoJSON-filer (Locations YYYY-MM.geojson), der viser de\nsensorer, der har været aktive, og deres omtrentlige placering på månedlig\nbasis. Tilsvarende måleværdier pr. måned er tilgængelige i CSV-filer (Water\nTemperatures YYYY-MM.csv).\n\nMåleværdifiler følger [FIWAREs specifikation for\nWaterQualityObserved](https://fiware%2ddatamodels.readthedocs.io/en/stable/Environment/WaterQualityObserved/doc/spec/index.html)\n.\n\n**Attributter Placeringer**\n\n  * `id` [sensoridentitet]\n  * `address` [sensorplacering (tekst)]\n  * `geometry` [sensorens omtrentlige position, type: Polygon, CRS: WGS84]\n\n**Attributter Vandtemperaturer**\n\n  * `type` [altid \"VandkvalitetObserveret\"]\n  * `id` [sensoridentitet]\n  * `address` [sensorplacering (tekst)]\n  * `dateObserved` [dato og tidspunkt (ISO 8601-format), hvornår måleværdien blev rapporteret]\n  * `temperature` [målt temperatur i grader Celsius]\n\n"@da;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/spatial> <http://www.geonames.org/2692965/malmoe.html>, _:b0__1569.
_:b0__1569 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#bbox> "POLYGON((12.8850967451 55.6421476735,13.1517619812 55.6421476735,13.1517619812 55.5022773196,12.8850967451 55.5022773196,12.8850967451 55.6421476735))"^^<http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#wktLiteral>;
